-- Russia to Tighten Oversight of Regional Banks, Kommersant Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2011-12-26T06:15:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/russia-to-tighten-oversight-of-regional-banks-kommersant-says.html
Russia ’s central bank plans to
tighten oversight of banks controlled by regional governments
after the state spent 300 billion rubles ($9.6 billion) to bail
out Bank of Moscow,  Kommersant  said, citing the regulator’s
Deputy Chairman Alexei Simanovsky.  Bank Rossii will look at a wider sample of loans to
evaluate the quality of regional lenders’ loan portfolios in
regular audits and may carry out unscheduled checks as well, the
Moscow-based daily reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
